'''Kobe Suitengū'''（こうべすいてんぐう） is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社}} ({{ill|Suiten-gu|ja|水天宮}}) located in {{ill|Hyogo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県}}{{ill|Kobe City|ja|神戸市}}{{ill|Nagata Ward|ja|長田区}}{{ill|Nagata Tenjin Town|ja|長田天神町}}.
== Enshrined Deities == It enshrines {{ill|Amenominakanushi|ja|天御中主神}} as its principal deity, and also enshrines {{ill|Antoku Emperor|ja|安徳天皇|1=Emperor Antoku|2=ja|3=安徳天皇|4=de|5=Antoku}}, {{ill|Heitokuji|ja|平徳子|lt=Kenreimonin (Heitokuji)|lt_ja=建礼門院（平徳子）}}, and {{ill|Second-Rank Nun Hira Tokushi|ja|平時子|lt=Second-Rank Nun Hira Tokushi|lt_ja=二位尼（にいのあま）平時子}}.
== History == According to the shrine legend, on Mount Tenjin—the location of this shrine—there is a tradition that during the time of {{ill|Kojidai|ja|神代}}, {{ill|Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主神}} descended from heaven, and the mountain was revered as a sacred mountain called Unade Hill (宇奈弖（うなで）の丘). In Taishō 3 ({{ill|1914|ja|1914th year}}), the shrine’s first {{ill|Chief Priest|ja|宮司}}, Nishigakuji, took the initiative to enshrine a branch spirit ({{ill|Bunrei|ja|分霊}}) from the Suiten-gu enshrined in {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県}}{{ill|Kurume City|ja|久留米市}} ({{ill|Suiten-gu (Kurume City)|ja|水天宮 (久留米市)|lt=Suiten-gu|lt_ja=水天宮}}). After an offering at Kusunoki in {{ill|Hyogo Ward|ja|兵庫区}}, it was temporarily enshrined at Kumano Shrine in {{ill|Nagata Ward|ja|長田区}}. In Taishō 11, October, a provisional main shrine was established on Unade Hill; and in the following April of Taishō 12, the shrine was transferred to its main location and enshrined as “Kobe Suitengū.”
== Sub-shrines == * Nagata Sha (ながたしゃ) Deity: {{ill|Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主神}} * Shirananaga Sha (しらながしゃ) Deity: {{ill|Ōmononushi|ja|大物主神}} * Tokuza-no-miya (とくさのみや) Deity: The sacred spirit of the founding Nishi family
== Festivals == * Spring Grand Festival: April 5 * Autumn Grand Festival: October 5
== Access == * About a 10‑minute walk from {{ill|Kobe Electric Railway|ja|神戸電鉄}}’s {{ill|Nagata Station|ja|長田駅 (神戸電鉄)|lt=Nagata Station|lt_ja=長田駅}} * Alight at in front of {{ill|Nagura Elementary School|ja|名倉小学校}} via {{ill|Kobe City Bus|ja|神戸市バス}} (as of December 2023, there is an onboard announcement)
