__NOTOC__ {{Shrine |Name = Kobe Suitengū |image = |Location = {{ill|Hyogo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft}}{{ill|Kobe City|ja|神戸市|qq=draft}}{{ill|Nagata Ward|ja|長田区|qq=draft}}{{ill|Nagata Tenjin Town|ja|長田天神町|qq=draft}}五丁目5番1号 |ISO = JP-28 |Latitude° = 34 | Latitude′ = 40 | Latitude″ = 55.4 | N (North) or S (South) = N |Longitude° = 135 | Longitude′ = 08 | Longitude″ = 46.3 | E (East) or W (West) = E |Enshrined Deity = {{ill|Amenominakanushi|ja|天御中主神|qq=draft}} |Rank = |Foundation = Unknown |Main Shrine = |Also Known As = Suiten-gu-san |Fuda Place = |Annual Festival = October 5 |Rituals = |Map = Japan Hyogo }}
'''Kobe Suitengū'''（こうべすいてんぐう） is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Suiten-gu|ja|水天宮|qq=draft}}) located in {{ill|Hyogo Prefecture|ja|兵庫県|qq=draft}}{{ill|Kobe City|ja|神戸市|qq=draft}}{{ill|Nagata Ward|ja|長田区|qq=draft}}{{ill|Nagata Tenjin Town|ja|長田天神町|qq=draft}}.
== Enshrined Deities == It enshrines {{ill|Amenominakanushi|ja|天御中主神|qq=draft}} as its principal deity, and also enshrines {{ill|Antoku Emperor|ja|安徳天皇|1=Emperor Antoku|2=ja|3=安徳天皇|4=de|5=Antoku|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Heitokuji|ja|平徳子|lt=Kenreimonin (Heitokuji)|lt_ja=建礼門院（平徳子）|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Second-Rank Nun Hira Tokushi|ja|平時子|lt=Second-Rank Nun Hira Tokushi|lt_ja=二位尼（にいのあま）平時子|qq=draft}}.
== History == According to the shrine legend, on Mount Tenjin—the location of this shrine—there is a tradition that during the time of {{ill|Kojidai|ja|神代|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主神|qq=draft}} descended from heaven, and the mountain was revered as a sacred mountain called Unade Hill (宇奈弖（うなで）の丘). In Taishō 3 ({{ill|1914|ja|1914th year|qq=draft}}), the shrine’s first {{ill|Chief Priest|ja|宮司|qq=draft}}, Nishigakuji, took the initiative to enshrine a branch spirit ({{ill|Bunrei|ja|分霊|qq=draft}}) from the Suiten-gu enshrined in {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|qq=draft}}{{ill|Kurume City|ja|久留米市|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Suiten-gu (Kurume City)|ja|水天宮 (久留米市)|lt=Suiten-gu|lt_ja=水天宮|qq=draft}}). After an offering at Kusunoki in {{ill|Hyogo Ward|ja|兵庫区|qq=draft}}, it was temporarily enshrined at Kumano Shrine in {{ill|Nagata Ward|ja|長田区|qq=draft}}. In Taishō 11, October, a provisional main shrine was established on Unade Hill; and in the following April of Taishō 12, the shrine was transferred to its main location and enshrined as “Kobe Suitengū.”
== Sub-shrines == * Nagata Sha (ながたしゃ) Deity: {{ill|Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主神|qq=draft}} * Shirananaga Sha (しらながしゃ) Deity: {{ill|Ōmononushi|ja|大物主神|qq=draft}} * Tokuza-no-miya (とくさのみや) Deity: The sacred spirit of the founding Nishi family
== Festivals == * Spring Grand Festival: April 5 * Autumn Grand Festival: October 5
== Access == * About a 10‑minute walk from {{ill|Kobe Electric Railway|ja|神戸電鉄|qq=draft}}’s {{ill|Nagata Station|ja|長田駅 (神戸電鉄)|lt=Nagata Station|lt_ja=長田駅|qq=draft}} * Alight at in front of {{ill|Nagura Elementary School|ja|名倉小学校|qq=draft}} via {{ill|Kobe City Bus|ja|神戸市バス|qq=draft}} (as of December 2023, there is an onboard announcement)
