'''Kobe Suitengū'''（こうべすいてんぐう） is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto Shrine]] ([[:en:Suitengū|Suiten-gu]]) located in [[:en:Hyōgo Prefecture|Hyōgo Prefecture]][[:en:Kobe|Kobe City]][[:en:Nagata-ku, Kobe|Nagata Ward]]{{ill|Nagata Tenjin Town|ja|長田天神町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagata Tenjin Town|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
== Enshrined Deities == It enshrines {{ill|Ame-no-Minakanushi|ja|天御中主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amenominakanushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天之御中主神}} as its principal deity, and also enshrines [[:en:Emperor Antoku|Emperor Antoku]], [[:en:Taira no Tokuko|Kenreimonin (Heitokuji)]], and [[:en:Taira no Tokiko|Second-Rank Nun Hira Tokushi]].
== History == According to the shrine legend, on Mount Tenjin—the location of this shrine—there is a tradition that during the time of {{ill|Kojidai|ja|神代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kojidai|qq=}}, {{ill|Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 事代主}} descended from heaven, and the mountain was revered as a sacred mountain called Unade Hill (宇奈弖（うなで）の丘). In Taishō 3 ([[:en:1914|1914]]), the shrine’s first {{ill|Chief Priest|ja|宮司|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chief Priest|qq=}}, Nishigakuji, took the initiative to enshrine a branch spirit ([[:en:Bunrei|Bunrei]]) from the Suiten-gu enshrined in [[:en:Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka Prefecture]][[:en:Kurume|Kurume City]] ([[:en:Kurume Suitengū|Suiten-gu]]). After an offering at Kusunoki in [[:en:Hyōgo-ku, Kobe|Hyōgo Ward]], it was temporarily enshrined at Kumano Shrine in [[:en:Nagata-ku, Kobe|Nagata Ward]]. In Taishō 11, October, a provisional main shrine was established on Unade Hill; and in the following April of Taishō 12, the shrine was transferred to its main location and enshrined as “Kobe Suitengū.”
== Sub-shrines == * Nagata Sha (ながたしゃ) Deity: {{ill|Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 事代主}} * Shirananaga Sha (しらながしゃ) Deity: {{ill|Ōmononushi|ja|大物主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmononushi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 大物主}} * Tokuza-no-miya (とくさのみや) Deity: The sacred spirit of the founding Nishi family
== Festivals == * Spring Grand Festival: April 5 * Autumn Grand Festival: October 5
